<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US">

<!-- @pageTitle = The Window -->

<!-- @include "global/head.kit"-->

<body class="project-page">
    <!-- @include "global/header_nav.kit" -->

    <main>
        <section class="hero">
            <div class="title-frame margins">
                <h1 class="project-title puzzle-type puzzle-auto" data-vertical-align="bottom">The Window</h1>
                <h5 class="desc">Philly's new hole in the wall</h5>
            </div>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w1_storefront-v2.jpg" alt="The Window storefront animation." class="hero-image" id="W1">
            <div class="tags-frame margins">
                <div class="tag">
                    <p>Logo</p>
                    <div class="squares"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="tag">
                    <p>Strategy</p>
                    <div class="squares"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="tag">
                    <p>Identity</p>
                    <div class="squares"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="adjectives margins">
                <p>familiar</p>
                <p>casual</p>
                <p>comforting</p>
                <p>quick</p>
                <p>satisfying</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="intro margins">
            <h5>
                We originally met with Oskar and Katrina about T-shirt designs for Bob & Barbara’s Lounge when they shared that they needed a brand identity and storefront design for the new restaurant they’d be opening up next&nbsp;door.
            </h5>
        </section>
        <section class="content margins" id="window">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w2_graphic-summary-v2.jpg" alt="The Window logo and graphic system." class="width4" id="W2">
            <p class="width2">
                The Window is the take-out restaurant for Philly landmark Bob & Barbara’s Lounge. B&B’s feels like it hasn’t changed in 60 years because it hasn’t. The Window is an extension of that feeling, just designed in the modern&nbsp;day.
            </p>
            <div class="small-img width3">
                <div class="vimeo-video width3" id="W3" style="--poster:url('assets/vimeo-thumbnails/w3.jpg');padding:100% 0 0 0;">
                    <iframe 
                        src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1146805454?background=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&muted=1&controls=0" 
                        frameborder="0" 
                        allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture;" 
                        title="w3_logo-anim">
                    </iframe>
                </div>
            </div>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w4_bite.jpg" alt="A close-up shot of a Window customer biting into a patty melt." class="width3" id="W4">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w5_ws-composition.jpg" alt="A variation of W logos." class="width6" id="W5">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w6_food-on-table-v2.jpg" alt="Tabletop image with various sandwiches and drinks on the table." class="width6" id="W6">
            <p class="width2">
                The menu consists of greasy comfort foods to soak up all the drinking. We developed a grid system based on the classic checkered-floor pattern of historic American diners and customized it to The Window by “goo-ifying” the squares together.
            </p>
            <div class="vimeo-video width4" id="W7" style="--poster:url('assets/vimeo-thumbnails/w7.jpg');padding:73.87% 0 0 0;">
                <iframe 
                    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1146805492?background=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&muted=1&controls=0" 
                    frameborder="0" 
                    allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture;" 
                    title="w7_diners">
                </iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="vimeo-video width4" id="W8" style="--poster:url('assets/vimeo-thumbnails/w8.jpg');padding:73.87% 0 0 0;">
                <iframe 
                    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1146805536?background=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&muted=1&controls=0" 
                    frameborder="0" 
                    allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture;" 
                    title="w8_square-corner-anim">
                </iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="width2 under-img">
                <img src="assets/project-pages/w9_tiles.jpg" alt="Diner tiles close up." class="width2" id="W9">
                <p>The food at The Window is a “twist on the classics.” This twist is not to be flashy, but modern.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="width2"></div>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w10_website-landing-page-v2.jpg" alt="The window website." class="width4" id="W10">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w11_top-down-table.jpg" alt="Customers eating at The Window." class="width3" id="W11">
            <div class="vimeo-video width3" id="W12" style="--poster:url('assets/vimeo-thumbnails/w12.jpg');padding:100% 0 0 0;">
                <iframe 
                    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1146805546?background=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&muted=1&controls=0" 
                    frameborder="0" 
                    allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture;" 
                    title="w12_grid-animation">
                </iframe>
            </div>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w13_typeface-demonstration.jpg" alt="The Window type system." class="width6" id="W13">
            <p class="width3">We also developed a typographic technique that is inspired by the physics of looking through a refracted glass window pane.</p>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w14_window-poster.png" alt="A frame sign stating: Tasty food at the window." class="width3" id="W14">
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w15_menu.jpg" alt="Two customers posing in front of the store menu." class="width6" id="W15">
            <div class="vimeo-video width6" id="W16" style="--poster:url('assets/vimeo-thumbnails/w16.jpg');padding:48.48% 0 0 0;">
                <iframe 
                    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1146805555?background=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&muted=1&controls=0" 
                    frameborder="0" 
                    allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture;" 
                    title="w16_reflection-type-final">
                </iframe>
            </div>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w17_reciept.jpg" alt="Recipt." class="width2" id="W17">
            <div class="vimeo-video width4" id="W18" style="--poster:url('assets/vimeo-thumbnails/w18.jpg');padding:73.87% 0 0 0;">
                <iframe 
                    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1146805566?background=1&autoplay=1&loop=1&muted=1&controls=0" 
                    frameborder="0" 
                    allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture;" 
                    title="w18_friends-having-fun">
                </iframe>
            </div>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w19_table-tent.jpg" alt="In store table tent" class="width4" id="W19">
            <p class="width2">There is a lot that humankind doesn’t agree on, but we can all agree that eating a delicious warm patty melt on a cold Friday night-out at the bar is the greatest feeling in the world.</p>
            <img src="assets/project-pages/w20_storefront-graphics.jpg" alt="A customer bringing their food to a table surrounded by people." class="width6" id="W20">

        </section>
